secondaryOutcomes.description:
Blood for the tests was drawn from basilic vein by medical personnel at the Rehabilitation Clinic.

CRP level:

* CRP below 5 mg / l (up to 10 mg / l - in obese people with hypertension) norm
* CRP above 40 mg / l - may indicate a mild viral infection or pregnancy;
* CRP above 200 mg / l - bacterial inflammation develops in the body;
* CRP above 500 mg / l - takes place in the situation of very serious infections with basic and bacterial infections and burns.
